\c 1
\p \v 1 The words of Amos, who was among the \x + \xo 1:1 \xt ch. 7:14, 15 \x*shepherds\f + \fr 1:1 \ft Or \fq sheep breeders\f* of \x + \xo 1:1 \xt 2 Sam. 14:2 \x*Tekoa, which he saw concerning Israel \x + \xo 1:1 \xt See Hos. 1:1 \x*in the days of \x + \xo 1:1 \xt 2 Kgs. 15:1, 13, 30; 2 Chr. 26:1 \x*Uzziah king of Judah and in the days of \x + \xo 1:1 \xt ch. 7:10; 2 Kgs. 14:23 \x*Jeroboam the son of Joash, king of Israel, two years\f + \fr 1:1 \ft Or \fq during two years\f* before \x + \xo 1:1 \xt Zech. 14:5; [Isa. 29:6]\x*the earthquake.
\s1 Judgment on Israel’s Neighbors
\m
\v 2 And he said:
\b
\q1 \x + \xo 1:2 \xt See Joel 3:16 \x*“The \nd Lord\nd* roars from Zion
\q2 and utters his voice from Jerusalem;
\q1 \x + \xo 1:2 \xt [Ps. 65:12] \x*the pastures of the shepherds mourn,
\q2 and the \x + \xo 1:2 \xt ch. 9:3 \x*top of \x + \xo 1:2 \xt See Josh. 19:26\x*Carmel withers.”
\b
\m
\v 3 Thus says the \nd Lord\nd*:
\b
\q1 \x + \xo 1:3 \xt ver. 9, 11, 13; ch. 2:1, 4, 6; Prov. 30:15, 18, 21, 29 \x*“For three transgressions of \x + \xo 1:3 \xt [Isa. 8:4] \x*Damascus,
\q2 and for four, \x + \xo 1:3 \xt [Isa. 8:4] \x*I will not revoke the punishment,\f + \fr 1:3 \ft Hebrew \fq I will not turn it back\ft ; also verses 6, 9, 11, 13\f*
\q1 because they have threshed \x + \xo 1:3 \xt ver. 13; [2 Kgs. 10:33; Isa. 21:10]\x*Gilead
\q2 with threshing sledges of iron.
\q1
\v 4 \x + \xo 1:4 \xt Jer. 49:27 \x*So I will send a fire upon the house of \x + \xo 1:4 \xt 2 Kgs. 13:24, 25\x*Hazael,
\q2 and it shall devour the strongholds of \x + \xo 1:4 \xt 2 Kgs. 13:24, 25\x*Ben-hadad.
\q1
\v 5 I will \x + \xo 1:5 \xt Jer. 51:30 \x*break the gate-bar of \x + \xo 1:5 \xt [See ver. 3 above] \x*Damascus,
\q2 and cut off the inhabitants from the Valley of \x + \xo 1:5 \xt See Hos. 4:15 \x*Aven,\f + \fr 1:5 \ft Or \fq On\f*
\q1 and him who holds the scepter from \x + \xo 1:5 \xt 2 Kgs. 19:12 \x*Beth-eden;
\q2 and the people of \x + \xo 1:5 \xt ch. 9:7; [2 Kgs. 16:9] \x*Syria shall go into exile to \x + \xo 1:5 \xt ch. 9:7; 2 Kgs. 16:9\x*Kir,”
\qr says the \nd Lord\nd*.
\b
\m
\v 6 Thus says the \nd Lord\nd*:
\b
\q1 \x + \xo 1:6 \xt [See ver. 3 above] \x*“For three transgressions of \x + \xo 1:6 \xt Jer. 47:1, 5; Zeph. 2:4; Zech. 9:5 \x*Gaza,
\q2 and for four, I will not revoke the punishment,
\q1 because \x + \xo 1:6 \xt 2 Chr. 28:18; See Joel 3:4-6\x*they carried into exile a whole people
\q2 to deliver them up to Edom.
\q1
\v 7 So I will send a fire upon the wall of \x + \xo 1:7 \xt [See ver. 6 above]\x*Gaza,
\q2 and it shall devour her strongholds.
\q1
\v 8 I will cut off the inhabitants from \x + \xo 1:8 \xt ch. 3:9; 1 Sam. 5:1\x*Ashdod,
\q2 and him who holds the scepter from Ashkelon;
\q1 I will turn my hand against Ekron,
\q2 and the remnant of the Philistines shall perish,”
\qr says the Lord \nd God\nd*.
\b
\m
\v 9 Thus says the \nd Lord\nd*:
\b
\q1 \x + \xo 1:9 \xt [See ver. 3 above] \x*“For three transgressions of \x + \xo 1:9 \xt See Joel 3:4\x*Tyre,
\q2 and for four, I will not revoke the punishment,
\q1 because they delivered up a whole people to Edom,
\q2 and did not remember the covenant of brotherhood.
\q1
\v 10 So I will send a fire upon the wall of \x + \xo 1:10 \xt [See ver. 9 above]\x*Tyre,
\q2 and it shall devour her strongholds.”
\b
\m
\v 11 Thus says the \nd Lord\nd*:
\b
\q1 \x + \xo 1:11 \xt [See ver. 3 above] \x*“For three transgressions of \x + \xo 1:11 \xt [2 Chr. 28:17] \x*Edom,
\q2 and for four, I will not revoke the punishment,
\q1 \x + \xo 1:11 \xt [2 Chr. 28:17] \x*because he pursued his brother with the sword
\q2 \x + \xo 1:11 \xt Ps. 137:7; [Joel 3:19; Mal. 1:4] \x*and cast off all pity,
\q1 \x + \xo 1:11 \xt Ezek. 35:5\x*and his anger tore perpetually,
\q2 \x + \xo 1:11 \xt Ezek. 35:5\x*and he kept his wrath forever.
\q1
\v 12 So I will send a fire upon \x + \xo 1:12 \xt Obad. 9; See 1 Chr. 1:45 \x*Teman,
\q2 and it shall devour the strongholds of \x + \xo 1:12 \xt Isa. 63:1; See 1 Chr. 1:44\x*Bozrah.”
\b
\m
\v 13 Thus says the \nd Lord\nd*:
\b
\q1 \x + \xo 1:13 \xt [See ver. 3 above] \x*“For three transgressions of the \x + \xo 1:13 \xt Jer. 49:1, 2; Zeph. 2:8, 9 \x*Ammonites,
\q2 and for four, I will not revoke the punishment,
\q1 because \x + \xo 1:13 \xt See Hos. 13:16 \x*they have ripped open pregnant women in \x + \xo 1:13 \xt ver. 3\x*Gilead,
\q2 that they might enlarge their border.
\q1
\v 14 So I will kindle a fire in the wall of \x + \xo 1:14 \xt 2 Sam. 11:1; 12:26; See Ezek. 21:20 \x*Rabbah,
\q2 \x + \xo 1:14 \xt [Ezek. 21:28, 29]\x*and it shall devour her strongholds,
\q1 with shouting on the day of battle,
\q2 \x + \xo 1:14 \xt [Ezek. 21:28, 29]\x*with a tempest in the day of the whirlwind;
\q1
\v 15 and \x + \xo 1:15 \xt Jer. 49:3\x*their king shall go into exile,
\q2 he and his princes\f + \fr 1:15 \ft Or \fq officials\f* together,”
\qr says the \nd Lord\nd*.
\b
\c 2
\m
\v 1 Thus says the \nd Lord\nd*:
\b
\q1 \x + \xo 2:1 \xt [See ch. 1:3 above] \x*“For three transgressions of \x + \xo 2:1 \xt Zeph. 2:8, 9; See Isa. 15 \x*Moab,
\q2 and for four, I will not revoke the punishment,\f + \fr 2:1 \ft Hebrew \fq I will not turn it back\ft ; also verses 4, 6\f*
\q1 because \x + \xo 2:1 \xt [2 Kgs. 3:27] \x*he burned to lime
\q2 the bones of the king of Edom.
\q1
\v 2 So I will send a fire upon Moab,
\q2 and it shall devour the strongholds of \x + \xo 2:2 \xt Jer. 48:24, 41\x*Kerioth,
\q1 and Moab shall die amid uproar,
\q2 amid shouting and the sound of the trumpet;
\q1
\v 3 \x + \xo 2:3 \xt [Jer. 48:7]\x*I will cut off the ruler from its midst,
\q2 and will kill \x + \xo 2:3 \xt [Jer. 48:7]\x*all its princes\f + \fr 2:3 \ft Or \fq officials\f* with him,”
\qr says the \nd Lord\nd*.
\s1 Judgment on Judah
\m
\v 4 Thus says the \nd Lord\nd*:
\b
\q1 \x + \xo 2:4 \xt See ch. 1:3 \x*“For three transgressions of Judah,
\q2 and for four, I will not revoke the punishment,
\q1 because \x + \xo 2:4 \xt Lev. 26:14, 15; Neh. 1:7; Ezek. 20:13, 16, 24; [Dan. 9:11] \x*they have rejected the law of the \nd Lord\nd*,
\q2 and have not kept his statutes,
\q1 but \x + \xo 2:4 \xt Jer. 16:19, 20; Rom. 1:25\x*their lies have led them astray,
\q2 those after which their fathers walked.
\q1
\v 5 So \x + \xo 2:5 \xt Jer. 17:27; Hos. 8:14\x*I will send a fire upon Judah,
\q2 and it shall devour the strongholds of Jerusalem.”
\s1 Judgment on Israel
\m
\v 6 Thus says the \nd Lord\nd*:
\b
\q1 \x + \xo 2:6 \xt [See ver. 4 above] \x*“For three transgressions of Israel,
\q2 and for four, I will not revoke the punishment,
\q1 because \x + \xo 2:6 \xt [Lev. 25:39; 2 Kgs. 4:1] \x*they sell the righteous for \x + \xo 2:6 \xt ch. 8:6\x*silver,
\q2 and the needy for a pair of sandals—
\q1
\v 7 those who trample the head of the poor \x + \xo 2:7 \xt Lam. 2:10 \x*into the dust of the earth
\q2 and \x + \xo 2:7 \xt ch. 5:12; Job 24:4; Isa. 10:2 \x*turn aside the way of the afflicted;
\q1 \x + \xo 2:7 \xt [1 Cor. 5:1]; See Ezek. 22:11\x*a man and his father go in to the same girl,
\q2 so that my holy name is profaned;
\q1
\v 8 they lay themselves down beside every altar
\q2 on garments \x + \xo 2:8 \xt See Ex. 22:26\x*taken in pledge,
\q1 and in the house of their God they drink
\q2 the wine of those who have been fined.
\b
\q1
\v 9 “Yet \x + \xo 2:9 \xt Deut. 2:31; Josh. 24:8; See Num. 21:21-25 \x*it was I who destroyed the Amorite before them,
\q2 \x + \xo 2:9 \xt [Num. 13:32, 33; Isa. 10:33] \x*whose height was like the height of the cedars
\q2 and who was as strong as the oaks;
\q1 \x + \xo 2:9 \xt [Job 18:16]\x*I destroyed his fruit above
\q2 and his roots beneath.
\q1
\v 10 \x + \xo 2:10 \xt ch. 3:1; Ex. 12:17, 51 \x*Also it was I who brought you up out of the land of Egypt
\q2 \x + \xo 2:10 \xt See Deut. 8:2 \x*and led you forty years in the wilderness,
\q2 \x + \xo 2:10 \xt [See ver. 9 above]\x*to possess the land of the Amorite.
\q1
\v 11 And I raised up some of your sons for prophets,
\q2 and some of your young men for \x + \xo 2:11 \xt Num. 6:2\x*Nazirites.
\q2 Is it not indeed so, O people of Israel?”
\qr declares the \nd Lord\nd*.
\b
\q1
\v 12 “But you made the Nazirites \x + \xo 2:12 \xt [Num. 6:3] \x*drink wine,
\q2 and commanded the prophets,
\q2 saying, \x + \xo 2:12 \xt ch. 7:13, 16; Isa. 30:10; Mic. 2:6\x*‘You shall not prophesy.’
\b
\q1
\v 13 “Behold, I will press you down in your place,
\q2 as a cart full of sheaves presses down.
\q1
\v 14 \x + \xo 2:14 \xt [ch. 9:1; Eccles. 9:11] \x*Flight shall perish from the swift,
\q2 \x + \xo 2:14 \xt [ch. 9:1; Eccles. 9:11] \x*and the strong shall not retain his strength,
\q2 \x + \xo 2:14 \xt [Ps. 33:16]\x*nor shall the mighty save his life;
\q1
\v 15 he who handles the bow shall not stand,
\q2 and he who is \x + \xo 2:15 \xt [2 Sam. 2:18] \x*swift of foot shall not save himself,
\q2 \x + \xo 2:15 \xt [Ps. 33:17]\x*nor shall he who rides the horse save his life;
\q1
\v 16 and he who is stout of heart among the mighty
\q2 shall flee away naked in that day,”
\qr declares the \nd Lord\nd*.
\c 3
\s1 Israel’s Guilt and Punishment
\p \v 1 \x + \xo 3:1 \xt ch. 7:16; [ch. 2:10]\x*Hear this word that the \nd Lord\nd* has spoken against you, O people of Israel, against the whole family that I brought up out of the land of Egypt:
\b
\q1
\v 2 \x + \xo 3:2 \xt Deut. 7:6; 10:15; Ps. 147:19, 20; [Hos. 5:3; 13:5; Mic. 2:3] \x*“You only have I known
\q2 of all the families of the earth;
\q1 \x + \xo 3:2 \xt [Matt. 10:15; 11:21, 22; Luke 10:13, 14; 12:47; Rom. 2:9]\x*therefore I will punish you
\q2 for all your iniquities.
\b
\q1
\v 3 “Do two walk together,
\q2 unless they have agreed to meet?
\q1
\v 4 Does a lion roar in the forest,
\q2 when he has no prey?
\q1 Does a young lion cry out from his den,
\q2 if he has taken nothing?
\q1
\v 5 Does a bird fall in a snare on the earth,
\q2 when there is no trap for it?
\q1 Does a snare spring up from the ground,
\q2 when it has taken nothing?
\q1
\v 6 \x + \xo 3:6 \xt Ezek. 33:4; See Joel 2:1 \x*Is a trumpet blown in a city,
\q2 and the people are not afraid?
\q1 \x + \xo 3:6 \xt [Isa. 45:7; Lam. 3:38; Mic. 1:12]\x*Does disaster come to a city,
\q2 unless the \nd Lord\nd* has done it?
\b
\q1
\v 7 “For the Lord \nd God\nd* does nothing
\q2 \x + \xo 3:7 \xt Gen. 18:17; [Jer. 15:1]\x*without revealing his secret
\q2 to his servants the prophets.
\q1
\v 8 The lion has roared;
\q2 who will not fear?
\q1 \x + \xo 3:8 \xt [Num. 22:38]\x*The Lord \nd God\nd* has spoken;
\q2 who can but prophesy?”
\b
\q1
\v 9 Proclaim to the strongholds in \x + \xo 3:9 \xt ch. 1:8 \x*Ashdod
\q2 and to the strongholds in the land of Egypt,
\q1 and say, “Assemble yourselves on \x + \xo 3:9 \xt ch. 4:1; 6:1; [1 Kgs. 16:24] \x*the mountains of Samaria,
\q2 and see the great tumults within her,
\q2 and \x + \xo 3:9 \xt Ps. 94:5, 6; 103:6; See 1 Kgs. 21:1-16\x*the oppressed in her midst.”
\q1
\v 10 “They do not know how to do right,” declares the \nd Lord\nd*,
\q2 \x + \xo 3:10 \xt [ch. 6:3; Isa. 3:14, 15]; See Mic. 6:10-12\x*“those who store up violence and robbery in their strongholds.”
\b
\m
\v 11 Therefore thus says the Lord \nd God\nd*:
\b
\q1 \x + \xo 3:11 \xt [2 Kgs. 17:5, 6]; See 2 Kgs. 18:9-12 \x*“An adversary shall surround the land
\q2 and bring down\f + \fr 3:11 \ft Hebrew \fq An adversary, one who surrounds the land—he shall bring down\f* your defenses from you,
\q2 and \x + \xo 3:11 \xt [Isa. 39:6]\x*your strongholds shall be plundered.”
\b
\p
\v 12 Thus says the \nd Lord\nd*: \x + \xo 3:12 \xt [Ex. 22:13] \x*“As the shepherd rescues from the mouth of the lion two legs, or a piece of an ear, \x + \xo 3:12 \xt See Jer. 31:8, 9 \x*so shall the people of Israel \x + \xo 3:12 \xt [ch. 6:4]\x*who dwell in Samaria be rescued, with the corner of a couch and part\f + \fr 3:12 \ft The meaning of the Hebrew word is uncertain\f* of a bed.
\b
\q1
\v 13 “Hear, \x + \xo 3:13 \xt [Ps. 50:7; 81:8] \x*and testify against the house of Jacob,”
\q2 declares the Lord \nd God\nd*, \x + \xo 3:13 \xt ch. 4:13; Ps. 80:4, 7, 14\x*the God of hosts,
\q1
\v 14 “that on the day I punish Israel for his transgressions,
\q2 \x + \xo 3:14 \xt [Hos. 10:15]; See 1 Kgs. 13:1-3 \x*I will punish the altars of Bethel,
\q1 and \x + \xo 3:14 \xt [2 Kgs. 23:15]\x*the horns of the altar shall be cut off
\q2 and fall to the ground.
\q1
\v 15 \x + \xo 3:15 \xt [ch. 6:11] \x*I will strike \x + \xo 3:15 \xt Jer. 36:22 \x*the winter house along with \x + \xo 3:15 \xt Judg. 3:20 \x*the summer house,
\q2 and \x + \xo 3:15 \xt 1 Kgs. 22:39; Ps. 45:8\x*the houses of ivory shall perish,
\q1 and the great houses\f + \fr 3:15 \ft Or \fq and many houses\f* shall come to an end,”
\qr declares the \nd Lord\nd*.
\b
\c 4
\q1 \v 1 “Hear this word, \x + \xo 4:1 \xt Ps. 22:12 \x*you cows of Bashan,
\q2 who are \x + \xo 4:1 \xt ch. 3:9; 6:1 \x*on the mountain of Samaria,
\q1 \x + \xo 4:1 \xt Hos. 5:11\x*who oppress the poor, \x + \xo 4:1 \xt Hos. 5:11\x*who crush the needy,
\q2 who say to your husbands, ‘Bring, that we may drink!’
\q1
\v 2 \x + \xo 4:2 \xt Ps. 89:35 \x*The Lord \nd God\nd* has sworn by his holiness
\q2 that, behold, the days are coming upon you,
\q1 \x + \xo 4:2 \xt [Jer. 16:16; Hab. 1:15]; See 2 Kgs. 19:28\x*when they shall take you away with hooks,
\q2 \x + \xo 4:2 \xt [Jer. 16:16; Hab. 1:15]; See 2 Kgs. 19:28\x*even the last of you with fishhooks.
\q1
\v 3 \x + \xo 4:3 \xt [Ezek. 12:5, 12]\x*And you shall go out through the breaches,
\q2 each one straight ahead;
\q2 and you shall be cast out into Harmon,”
\qr declares the \nd Lord\nd*.
\b
\q1
\v 4 \x + \xo 4:4 \xt [ch. 5:5; Ezek. 20:39; Matt. 23:32] \x*“Come to Bethel, and transgress;
\q2 to \x + \xo 4:4 \xt [ch. 5:5; Hos. 4:15; 9:15; 12:11] \x*Gilgal, and multiply transgression;
\q1 \x + \xo 4:4 \xt [ch. 5:5; Ezek. 20:39; Matt. 23:32] \x*bring your \x + \xo 4:4 \xt Num. 28:3, 4; [Jer. 7:21]\x*sacrifices every morning,
\q2 your tithes every three days;
\q1
\v 5 offer a sacrifice of thanksgiving of \x + \xo 4:5 \xt Lev. 7:13 \x*that which is leavened,
\q2 and proclaim \x + \xo 4:5 \xt Ex. 35:29; Lev. 22:18, 21; Deut. 12:6 \x*freewill offerings, publish them;
\q2 \x + \xo 4:5 \xt [Ps. 81:11, 12]\x*for so you love to do, O people of Israel!”
\qr declares the Lord \nd God\nd*.
\s1 Israel Has Not Returned to the \nd Lord\nd*
\q1
\v 6 “I gave you cleanness of teeth in all your cities,
\q2 and \x + \xo 4:6 \xt [Deut. 28:57; Lam. 2:12] \x*lack of bread in all your places,
\q1 \x + \xo 4:6 \xt Jer. 15:7; Hag. 2:17\x*yet you did not return to me,”
\qr declares the \nd Lord\nd*.
\b
\q1
\v 7 “I also \x + \xo 4:7 \xt Jer. 3:3; [Joel 2:23] \x*withheld the rain from you
\q2 when there were yet three months to the harvest;
\q1 \x + \xo 4:7 \xt [Ex. 9:26]\x*I would send rain on one city,
\q2 and send no rain on another city;
\q1 one field would have rain,
\q2 and the field on which it did not rain would wither;
\q1
\v 8 so two or three cities \x + \xo 4:8 \xt [ch. 8:12] \x*would wander to another city
\q2 to drink water, and would not be satisfied;
\q1 \x + \xo 4:8 \xt [See ver. 6 above]\x*yet you did not return to me,”
\qr declares the \nd Lord\nd*.
\b
\q1
\v 9 \x + \xo 4:9 \xt Deut. 28:22; Hag. 2:17 \x*“I struck you with blight and mildew;
\q2 your many gardens and your vineyards,
\q2 your fig trees and your olive trees \x + \xo 4:9 \xt Joel 1:4 \x*the locust devoured;
\q1 \x + \xo 4:9 \xt [See ver. 6 above]\x*yet you did not return to me,”
\qr declares the \nd Lord\nd*.
\b
\q1
\v 10 “I sent among you a pestilence \x + \xo 4:10 \xt Deut. 28:27, 60; [Ex. 12:29; Ps. 78:50; Isa. 10:24, 26] \x*after the manner of Egypt;
\q2 I killed your young men with the sword,
\q1 and \x + \xo 4:10 \xt 2 Kgs. 13:7 \x*carried away your horses,\f + \fr 4:10 \ft Hebrew \fq along with the captivity of your horses\f*
\q2 and \x + \xo 4:10 \xt [Joel 2:20] \x*I made the stench of your camp go up into your nostrils;
\q1 \x + \xo 4:10 \xt [See ver. 6 above]\x*yet you did not return to me,”
\qr declares the \nd Lord\nd*.
\b
\q1
\v 11 “I overthrew some of you,
\q2 \x + \xo 4:11 \xt [Isa. 13:19] \x*as when God overthrew Sodom and Gomorrah,
\q2 and you were \x + \xo 4:11 \xt Zech. 3:2; [Jude 23] \x*as a brand\f + \fr 4:11 \ft That is, a burning stick\f* plucked out of the burning;
\q1 \x + \xo 4:11 \xt [See ver. 6 above]\x*yet you did not return to me,”
\qr declares the \nd Lord\nd*.
\b
\q1
\v 12 “Therefore thus I will do to you, O Israel;
\q2 because I will do this to you,
\q2 prepare to meet your God, O Israel!”
\b
\q1
\v 13 For behold, \x + \xo 4:13 \xt [Ps. 102:25] \x*he who forms the mountains and creates the wind,
\q2 and \x + \xo 4:13 \xt [Ps. 139:2] \x*declares to man what is his thought,
\q1 \x + \xo 4:13 \xt [ch. 5:8; 8:9] \x*who makes the morning darkness,
\q2 and \x + \xo 4:13 \xt Isa. 58:14; Mic. 1:3 \x*treads on the heights of the earth—
\q2 \x + \xo 4:13 \xt ch. 3:13; 5:8; 9:6; See Jer. 10:16\x*the \nd Lord\nd*, the God of hosts, is his name!
\c 5
\s1 Seek the \nd Lord\nd* and Live
\p \v 1 Hear this word that I \x + \xo 5:1 \xt Ezek. 19:1\x*take up over you in lamentation, O house of Israel:
\b
\q1
\v 2 “Fallen, no more to rise,
\q2 is \x + \xo 5:2 \xt Lam. 2:1; [Isa. 47:1]\x*the virgin Israel;
\q1 forsaken on her land,
\q2 with none to raise her up.”
\b
\m
\v 3 For thus says the Lord \nd God\nd*:
\b
\q1 “The city that went out a thousand
\q2 shall have a hundred left,
\q1 and that which went out a hundred
\q2 shall have ten left
\q2 to the house of Israel.”
\b
\m
\v 4 For thus says the \nd Lord\nd* to the house of Israel:
\b
\q1 \x + \xo 5:4 \xt 2 Chr. 15:2; Isa. 55:6; Zeph. 2:3\x*“Seek me and live;
\q2
\v 5 but do not seek \x + \xo 5:5 \xt See ch. 4:4 \x*Bethel,
\q1 and do not enter into \x + \xo 5:5 \xt See ch. 4:4 \x*Gilgal
\q2 or cross over to \x + \xo 5:5 \xt ch. 8:14\x*Beersheba;
\q1 for \x + \xo 5:5 \xt See ch. 4:4 \x*Gilgal shall surely go into exile,
\q2 and \x + \xo 5:5 \xt See ch. 4:4 \x*Bethel shall come to nothing.”
\b
\q1
\v 6 \x + \xo 5:6 \xt [See ver. 4 above] \x*Seek the \nd Lord\nd* and live,
\q2 \x + \xo 5:6 \xt [Isa. 9:18, 19] \x*lest he break out like fire in the house of Joseph,
\q2 and it devour, with none to quench it for \x + \xo 5:6 \xt [See ver. 5 above]\x*Bethel,
\q1
\v 7 O \x + \xo 5:7 \xt [ch. 6:12]\x*you who turn justice to wormwood\f + \fr 5:7 \ft Or \fq to bitter fruit\f*
\q2 and cast down righteousness to the earth!
\b
\q1
\v 8 He who made the \x + \xo 5:8 \xt Job 9:9; 38:31 \x*Pleiades and Orion,
\q2 and turns deep darkness into the morning
\q2 and \x + \xo 5:8 \xt Ps. 104:20; [ch. 4:13; 8:9] \x*darkens the day into night,
\q1 who \x + \xo 5:8 \xt ch. 9:6; [Gen. 6:17; Ps. 104:6, 7] \x*calls for the waters of the sea
\q2 \x + \xo 5:8 \xt ch. 9:6; [Gen. 6:17; Ps. 104:6, 7] \x*and pours them out on the surface of the earth,
\q1 \x + \xo 5:8 \xt See ch. 4:13\x*the \nd Lord\nd* is his name;
\q1
\v 9 \x + \xo 5:9 \xt [Jer. 50:32]\x*who makes destruction flash forth against the strong,
\q2 so that destruction comes upon the fortress.
\b
\q1
\v 10 \x + \xo 5:10 \xt Isa. 29:21; [Prov. 15:5, 10] \x*They hate him who reproves \x + \xo 5:10 \xt See Ruth 4:1 \x*in the gate,
\q2 and they \x + \xo 5:10 \xt [1 Kgs. 22:8]\x*abhor him who speaks the truth.
\q1
\v 11 Therefore because you \x + \xo 5:11 \xt [James 2:6] \x*trample on\f + \fr 5:11 \ft Or \fq you tax\f* the poor
\q2 and you exact taxes of grain from him,
\q1 \x + \xo 5:11 \xt Deut. 28:30, 39; Mic. 6:15; Zeph. 1:13\x*you have built houses of hewn stone,
\q2 but you shall not dwell in them;
\q1 \x + \xo 5:11 \xt Deut. 28:30, 39; Mic. 6:15; Zeph. 1:13\x*you have planted pleasant vineyards,
\q2 but you shall not drink their wine.
\q1
\v 12 For I know how many are your transgressions
\q2 and how great are your sins—
\q1 you who afflict the righteous, who \x + \xo 5:12 \xt 1 Sam. 8:3; 12:3; [Ps. 26:10] \x*take a bribe,
\q2 and \x + \xo 5:12 \xt ch. 2:7; Isa. 29:21 \x*turn aside the needy \x + \xo 5:12 \xt [See ver. 10 above]\x*in the gate.
\q1
\v 13 Therefore he who is prudent will \x + \xo 5:13 \xt [Eccles. 3:7] \x*keep silent in such a time,
\q2 \x + \xo 5:13 \xt Mic. 2:3\x*for it is an evil time.
\b
\q1
\v 14 \x + \xo 5:14 \xt [Deut. 30:15, 19; Zeph. 2:3] \x*Seek good, and not evil,
\q2 that you may live;
\q1 and so the \nd Lord\nd*, \x + \xo 5:14 \xt ch. 3:13\x*the God of hosts, will be with you,
\q2 as you have said.
\q1
\v 15 \x + \xo 5:15 \xt Ps. 97:10; Rom. 12:9 \x*Hate evil, and love good,
\q2 and establish justice \x + \xo 5:15 \xt [See ver. 10 above] \x*in the gate;
\q1 \x + \xo 5:15 \xt Joel 2:14; [Ex. 32:30]\x*it may be that the \nd Lord\nd*, the God of hosts,
\q2 will be gracious to the remnant of Joseph.
\b
\m
\v 16 Therefore thus says the \nd Lord\nd*, \x + \xo 5:16 \xt [See ver. 14 above] \x*the God of hosts, the Lord:
\b
\q1 “In all the squares \x + \xo 5:16 \xt [Jer. 9:17, 18]\x*there shall be wailing,
\q2 and in all the streets they shall say, ‘Alas! Alas!’
\q1 They shall call the farmers to mourning
\q2 and \x + \xo 5:16 \xt [Jer. 9:17, 18]\x*to wailing those who are skilled in lamentation,
\q1
\v 17 and in all vineyards there shall be wailing,
\q2 for \x + \xo 5:17 \xt Ex. 12:12\x*I will pass through your midst,”
\qr says the \nd Lord\nd*.
\s1 Let Justice Roll Down
\q1
\v 18 Woe to you who desire \x + \xo 5:18 \xt See Joel 1:15 \x*the day of the \nd Lord\nd*!
\q2 Why would you have the day of the \nd Lord\nd*?
\q1 \x + \xo 5:18 \xt See Joel 2:1, 2\x*It is darkness, and not light,
\q2
\v 19 \x + \xo 5:19 \xt [Isa. 24:18; Jer. 48:44]\x*as if a man fled from a lion,
\q2 and a bear met him,
\q1 or went into the house and leaned his hand against the wall,
\q2 and a serpent bit him.
\q1
\v 20 \x + \xo 5:20 \xt [See ver. 18 above]\x*Is not the day of the \nd Lord\nd* darkness, and not light,
\q2 and gloom with no brightness in it?
\b
\q1
\v 21 \x + \xo 5:21 \xt Isa. 1:14; [Jer. 6:20]\x*“I hate, I despise your feasts,
\q2 and I take no delight in your solemn assemblies.
\q1
\v 22 \x + \xo 5:22 \xt Ps. 51:16, 17; Isa. 1:11\x*Even though you offer me your burnt offerings and grain offerings,
\q2 I will not accept them;
\q1 and the peace offerings of your fattened animals,
\q2 I will not look upon them.
\q1
\v 23 Take away from me the noise of your songs;
\q2 to \x + \xo 5:23 \xt [ch. 6:5; 8:3; Isa. 5:12]\x*the melody of your harps I will not listen.
\q1
\v 24 But let justice roll down like waters,
\q2 and righteousness like an ever-flowing stream.
\b
\p
\v 25 \x + \xo 5:25 \xt Cited Acts 7:42, 43\x*“Did you bring to me sacrifices and offerings during the forty years in the wilderness, O house of Israel?
\v 26 \x + \xo 5:26 \xt [Deut. 32:17; Ezek. 20:16, 24] \x*You \x + \xo 5:26 \xt [Isa. 46:7]\x*shall take up Sikkuth your king, and Kiyyun your star-god—your images that you made for yourselves,
\v 27 \x + \xo 5:27 \xt 2 Kgs. 17:6 \x*and I will send you into exile beyond Damascus,” says the \nd Lord\nd*, whose name is \x + \xo 5:27 \xt [See ver. 14 above]\x*the God of hosts.
\c 6
\s1 Woe to Those at Ease in Zion
\q1 \v 1 \x + \xo 6:1 \xt Isa. 32:9; Zeph. 1:12; Luke 6:24; James 5:1 \x*“Woe to those who are at ease in Zion,
\q2 and to those who feel secure on \x + \xo 6:1 \xt ch. 3:9; 4:1 \x*the mountain of Samaria,
\q1 \x + \xo 6:1 \xt [Ezek. 22:6] \x*the notable men of \x + \xo 6:1 \xt See Ex. 19:5\x*the first of the nations,
\q2 to whom the house of Israel comes!
\q1
\v 2 Pass over to \x + \xo 6:2 \xt Gen. 10:10; Isa. 10:9 \x*Calneh, and see,
\q2 and from there go to \x + \xo 6:2 \xt 1 Kgs. 8:65; 2 Kgs. 18:34; Isa. 10:9 \x*Hamath the great;
\q2 then go down to \x + \xo 6:2 \xt See 1 Sam. 17:4 \x*Gath of the Philistines.
\q1 \x + \xo 6:2 \xt [Nah. 3:8]\x*Are you better than these kingdoms?
\q2 Or is their territory greater than your territory,
\q1
\v 3 \x + \xo 6:3 \xt [ch. 9:10; Ezek. 12:27] \x*O you who put far away the day of disaster
\q2 \x + \xo 6:3 \xt See ch. 3:10\x*and bring near the seat of violence?
\b
\q1
\v 4 “Woe to those \x + \xo 6:4 \xt [ch. 3:12] \x*who lie on \x + \xo 6:4 \xt [Esth. 1:6] \x*beds of ivory
\q2 \x + \xo 6:4 \xt [ch. 3:12] \x*and stretch themselves out on their couches,
\q1 and eat lambs from the flock
\q2 \x + \xo 6:4 \xt [James 5:5]\x*and calves from the midst of the stall,
\q1
\v 5 \x + \xo 6:5 \xt See ch. 5:23\x*who sing idle songs to the sound of the harp
\q2 and like David \x + \xo 6:5 \xt See ch. 5:23\x*invent for themselves instruments of music,
\q1
\v 6 \x + \xo 6:6 \xt [Isa. 5:12] \x*who drink wine in bowls
\q2 and \x + \xo 6:6 \xt [Dan. 10:3]\x*anoint themselves with the finest oils,
\q2 but are not grieved over the ruin of Joseph!
\q1
\v 7 \x + \xo 6:7 \xt ch. 7:11, 17\x*Therefore they shall now be the first of those who go into exile,
\q2 and the revelry of those who stretch themselves out shall pass away.”
\b
\m
\v 8 \x + \xo 6:8 \xt Jer. 22:5; 51:14 \x*The Lord \nd God\nd* has sworn by himself, declares the \nd Lord\nd*, the God of hosts:
\b
\q1 “I abhor \x + \xo 6:8 \xt ch. 8:7; [Ps. 47:4] \x*the pride of Jacob
\q2 and hate his strongholds,
\q2 \x + \xo 6:8 \xt [Jer. 17:3]\x*and I will deliver up the city and all that is in it.”
\b
\p
\v 9 And \x + \xo 6:9 \xt [ch. 3:3]\x*if ten men remain in one house, they shall die.
\v 10 And when one’s relative, \x + \xo 6:10 \xt See 1 Sam. 31:12 \x*the one who anoints him for burial, shall take him up to bring the bones out of the house, and shall say to him who is in the innermost parts of the house, “Is there still anyone with you?” he shall say, “No”; and he shall say, \x + \xo 6:10 \xt [ch. 5:13; 8:3]\x*“Silence! We must not mention the name of the \nd Lord\nd*.”
\b
\q1
\v 11 For behold, the \nd Lord\nd* commands,
\q2 and \x + \xo 6:11 \xt [ch. 3:15]\x*the great house shall be struck down into fragments,
\q2 and the little house into bits.
\q1
\v 12 Do horses run on rocks?
\q2 Does one plow there\f + \fr 6:12 \ft Or \fq the sea\f* with oxen?
\q1 \x + \xo 6:12 \xt [ch. 5:7] \x*But you have turned justice into \x + \xo 6:12 \xt Deut. 29:18\x*poison
\q2 \x + \xo 6:12 \xt [ch. 5:7] \x*and the fruit of righteousness into wormwood\f + \fr 6:12 \ft Or \fq into bitter fruit\f*—
\q1
\v 13 you who rejoice in Lo-debar,\f + \fr 6:13 \fq Lo-debar \ft means \fq nothing\f*
\q2 who say, \x + \xo 6:13 \xt [1 Kgs. 22:11; Mic. 4:13]\x*“Have we not by our own strength
\q2 captured Karnaim\f + \fr 6:13 \fq Karnaim \ft means \fq horns \ft (a symbol of strength)\f* for ourselves?”
\q1
\v 14 “For behold, \x + \xo 6:14 \xt [Jer. 5:15] \x*I will raise up against you a nation,
\q2 O house of Israel,” declares the \nd Lord\nd*, the God of hosts;
\q1 “and they shall oppress you from \x + \xo 6:14 \xt 2 Kgs. 14:25 \x*Lebo-hamath
\q2 to the Brook of \x + \xo 6:14 \xt See Deut. 1:1\x*the Arabah.”
\c 7
\s1 Warning Visions
\p \v 1 \x + \xo 7:1 \xt ch. 8:1 \x*This is what the Lord \nd God\nd* showed me: behold, \x + \xo 7:1 \xt [Joel 1:4]; See Ex. 10:4\x*he was forming locusts when the latter growth was just beginning to sprout, and behold, it was the latter growth after the king’s mowings.
\v 2 When they had finished eating the grass of the land, I said,
\b
\q1 “O Lord \nd God\nd*, please forgive!
\q2 \x + \xo 7:2 \xt [Ps. 130:3]\x*How can Jacob stand?
\q2 He is so small!”
\q1
\v 3 \x + \xo 7:3 \xt [Deut. 32:36; Joel 2:13]\x*The \nd Lord\nd* relented concerning this:
\q2 “It shall not be,” said the \nd Lord\nd*.
\b
\p
\v 4 \x + \xo 7:4 \xt [See ver. 1 above] \x*This is what the Lord \nd God\nd* showed me: behold, the Lord \nd God\nd* was calling \x + \xo 7:4 \xt [Rev. 8:7, 8]\x*for a judgment by fire, and it devoured the great deep and was eating up the land.
\v 5 Then I said,
\b
\q1 “O Lord \nd God\nd*, please cease!
\q2 \x + \xo 7:5 \xt [See ver. 2 above]\x*How can Jacob stand?
\q2 He is so small!”
\q1
\v 6 \x + \xo 7:6 \xt [See ver. 3 above]\x*The \nd Lord\nd* relented concerning this:
\q2 “This also shall not be,” said the Lord \nd God\nd*.
\b
\p
\v 7 \x + \xo 7:7 \xt [See ver. 1 above] \x*This is what he showed me: behold, the Lord was standing beside a wall built with \x + \xo 7:7 \xt [ver. 17]; See 2 Kgs. 21:13\x*a plumb line, with a plumb line in his hand.
\v 8 And the \nd Lord\nd* said to me, \x + \xo 7:8 \xt ch. 8:2 \x*“Amos, what do you see?” And I said, “A plumb line.” Then the Lord said,
\b
\q1 “Behold, I am setting \x + \xo 7:8 \xt [See ver. 7 above]\x*a plumb line
\q2 in the midst of my people Israel;
\q2 \x + \xo 7:8 \xt ch. 8:2 \x*I will never again pass by them;
\q1
\v 9 \x + \xo 7:9 \xt Gen. 26:23, 25 \x*the high places of Isaac shall be made desolate,
\q2 and the sanctuaries of Israel shall be laid waste,
\q2 and I will rise against \x + \xo 7:9 \xt See 2 Kgs. 15:8-12\x*the house of Jeroboam with the sword.”
\s1 Amos Accused
\p
\v 10 Then Amaziah \x + \xo 7:10 \xt 1 Kgs. 12:32 \x*the priest of Bethel sent to \x + \xo 7:10 \xt ch. 1:1 \x*Jeroboam king of Israel, saying, “Amos has \x + \xo 7:10 \xt [Jer. 38:4]\x*conspired against you in the midst of the house of Israel. The land is not able to bear all his words.
\v 11 For thus Amos has said,
\b
\q1 “‘Jeroboam shall die by the sword,
\q2 and \x + \xo 7:11 \xt ch. 6:7\x*Israel must go into exile
\q2 away from his land.’”
\b
\m
\v 12 And Amaziah said to Amos, \x + \xo 7:12 \xt See 1 Sam. 9:9 \x*“O seer, go, flee away \x + \xo 7:12 \xt [ch. 1:1] \x*to the land of Judah, and \x + \xo 7:12 \xt [Mic. 3:5, 11]\x*eat bread there, and prophesy there,
\v 13 but \x + \xo 7:13 \xt See ch. 2:12 \x*never again prophesy at Bethel, for \x + \xo 7:13 \xt See 1 Kgs. 12:29–13:1\x*it is the king’s sanctuary, and it is a temple of the kingdom.”
\p
\v 14 Then Amos answered and said to Amaziah, \x + \xo 7:14 \xt ch. 1:1; [Zech. 13:5] \x*“I was\f + \fr 7:14 \ft Or \fq am\ft ; twice in this verse\f* no prophet, nor a prophet’s son, but \x + \xo 7:14 \xt ch. 1:1\x*I was a herdsman and a dresser of sycamore figs.
\v 15 \x + \xo 7:15 \xt [Ps. 78:71]\x*But the \nd Lord\nd* took me from following the flock, and the \nd Lord\nd* said to me, ‘Go, prophesy to my people Israel.’
\v 16 \x + \xo 7:16 \xt ch. 3:1 \x*Now therefore hear the word of the \nd Lord\nd*.
\b
\q1 “You say, \x + \xo 7:16 \xt [See ver. 12 above] \x*‘Do not prophesy against Israel,
\q2 and \x + \xo 7:16 \xt Ezek. 20:46; 21:2; Mic. 2:6 \x*do not preach against the house of \x + \xo 7:16 \xt [ver. 9]\x*Isaac.’
\b
\m
\v 17 \x + \xo 7:17 \xt [Jer. 28:16; 29:21, 31, 32] \x*Therefore thus says the \nd Lord\nd*:
\b
\q1 “‘Your wife shall be a prostitute in the city,
\q2 and your sons and your daughters shall fall by the sword,
\q2 and your land \x + \xo 7:17 \xt [ver. 7, 8] \x*shall be divided up with a measuring line;
\q1 you yourself shall die in an unclean land,
\q2 and \x + \xo 7:17 \xt [See ver. 11 above]\x*Israel shall surely go into exile away from its land.’”
\c 8
\s1 The Coming Day of Bitter Mourning
\p \v 1 \x + \xo 8:1 \xt ch. 7:1\x*This is what the Lord \nd God\nd* showed me: behold, a basket of summer fruit.
\v 2 And he said, \x + \xo 8:2 \xt ch. 7:8 \x*“Amos, what do you see?” And I said, \x + \xo 8:2 \xt [Jer. 24:1; Mic. 7:1] \x*“A basket of summer fruit.” Then the \nd Lord\nd* said to me,
\b
\q1 \x + \xo 8:2 \xt Lam. 4:18\x*“The end\f + \fr 8:2 \ft The Hebrew words for \fq end \ft and \fq summer fruit \ft sound alike\f* has come upon my people Israel;
\q2 I will never again pass by them.
\q1
\v 3 \x + \xo 8:3 \xt [ch. 5:23] \x*The songs of the temple\f + \fr 8:3 \ft Or \fq palace\f* \x + \xo 8:3 \xt [Jer. 47:2] \x*shall become wailings\f + \fr 8:3 \ft Or \fq The singing women of the palace shall wail\f* in that day,”
\qr declares the Lord \nd God\nd*.
\q1 \x + \xo 8:3 \xt [ch. 6:9] \x*“So many dead bodies!”
\q1 “They are thrown everywhere!”
\q1 \x + \xo 8:3 \xt [ch. 6:10; Jer. 16:4, 6]\x*“Silence!”
\b
\q1
\v 4 Hear this, \x + \xo 8:4 \xt [Ps. 14:4]\x*you who trample on the needy
\q2 and bring the poor of the land to an end,
\q1
\v 5 saying, “When will \x + \xo 8:5 \xt See Num. 28:11 \x*the new moon be over,
\q2 that we may sell grain?
\q1 And \x + \xo 8:5 \xt [Neh. 13:15, 16] \x*the Sabbath,
\q2 that we may offer wheat for sale,
\q1 that we may make \x + \xo 8:5 \xt Ezek. 45:10; Mic. 6:10, 11; See Hos. 12:7\x*the ephah small and the shekel\f + \fr 8:5 \ft An \fq ephah \ft was about 3/5 bushel or 22 liters; a \fq shekel \ft was about 2/5 ounce or 11 grams\f* great
\q2 and deal deceitfully with false balances,
\q1
\v 6 that we may buy the poor for \x + \xo 8:6 \xt ch. 2:6\x*silver
\q2 and the needy for a pair of sandals
\q2 and sell the chaff of the wheat?”
\b
\q1
\v 7 The \nd Lord\nd* has sworn by \x + \xo 8:7 \xt ch. 6:8 \x*the pride of Jacob:
\q1 “Surely \x + \xo 8:7 \xt Hos. 8:13; 9:9\x*I will never forget any of their deeds.
\q1
\v 8 \x + \xo 8:8 \xt [Hos. 4:3] \x*Shall not the land tremble on this account,
\q2 and everyone mourn who dwells in it,
\q1 \x + \xo 8:8 \xt ch. 9:5 \x*and all of it rise like the Nile,
\q2 and be tossed about \x + \xo 8:8 \xt [Zech. 10:11]\x*and sink again, like the Nile of Egypt?”
\b
\q1
\v 9 “And on that day,” declares the Lord \nd God\nd*,
\q2 \x + \xo 8:9 \xt Jer. 15:9; Mic. 3:6; Matt. 24:29; [ch. 4:13; 5:8]\x*“I will make the sun go down at noon
\q2 and darken the earth in broad daylight.
\q1
\v 10 \x + \xo 8:10 \xt [Jer. 7:34; 16:9; Hos. 2:11] \x*I will turn your feasts into mourning
\q2 and all your songs into lamentation;
\q1 \x + \xo 8:10 \xt Isa. 3:24 \x*I will bring sackcloth on every waist
\q2 \x + \xo 8:10 \xt Isa. 3:24 \x*and baldness on every head;
\q1 \x + \xo 8:10 \xt Jer. 6:26; Zech. 12:10\x*I will make it like the mourning for an only son
\q2 and the end of it like a bitter day.
\b
\q1
\v 11 “Behold, the days are coming,” declares the Lord \nd God\nd*,
\q2 “when \x + \xo 8:11 \xt [Isa. 8:20, 21] \x*I will send a famine on the land—
\q1 not a famine of bread, nor a thirst for water,
\q2 \x + \xo 8:11 \xt [Ps. 74:9; Prov. 29:18; Mic. 3:7]\x*but of hearing the words of the \nd Lord\nd*.
\q1
\v 12 \x + \xo 8:12 \xt [See ver. 11 above] \x*They shall wander from sea to sea,
\q2 and from north to east;
\q1 they shall run to and fro, to seek the word of the \nd Lord\nd*,
\q2 \x + \xo 8:12 \xt [ch. 4:8]\x*but they shall not find it.
\b
\q1
\v 13 \x + \xo 8:13 \xt Isa. 51:20 \x*“In that day the lovely virgins and the young men
\q2 shall \x + \xo 8:13 \xt [Jonah 4:8]\x*faint for thirst.
\q1
\v 14 Those who swear by \x + \xo 8:14 \xt Deut. 9:21; 1 Kgs. 12:29, 30; Hos. 10:8 \x*the Guilt of Samaria,
\q2 and say, ‘As your god lives, O Dan,’
\q1 and, ‘As \x + \xo 8:14 \xt [Acts 9:2] \x*the Way of \x + \xo 8:14 \xt ch. 5:5\x*Beersheba lives,’
\q2 they shall fall, and never rise again.”
\c 9
\s1 The Destruction of Israel
\p \v 1 I saw the Lord standing beside\f + \fr 9:1 \ft Or \fq on\f* the altar, and he said:
\b
\q1 \x + \xo 9:1 \xt Zeph. 2:14 \x*“Strike the capitals until \x + \xo 9:1 \xt Zeph. 2:14 \x*the thresholds \x + \xo 9:1 \xt [Isa. 6:4] \x*shake,
\q2 \x + \xo 9:1 \xt See Judg. 16:26-30 \x*and shatter them on the heads of all the people;\f + \fr 9:1 \ft Hebrew \fq all of them\f*
\q1 and those who are left of them I will kill with the sword;
\q2 \x + \xo 9:1 \xt [ch. 2:14]\x*not one of them shall flee away;
\q2 not one of them shall escape.
\b
\q1
\v 2 \x + \xo 9:2 \xt [Ps. 139:8-10]\x*“If they dig into Sheol,
\q2 from there shall my hand take them;
\q1 \x + \xo 9:2 \xt [Ps. 139:8-10]\x*if they climb up to heaven,
\q2 from there I will bring them down.
\q1
\v 3 If they hide themselves on \x + \xo 9:3 \xt ch. 1:2 \x*the top of Carmel,
\q2 from there I will search them out and take them;
\q1 \x + \xo 9:3 \xt [Job 26:5]\x*and if they hide from my sight at the bottom of the sea,
\q2 there I will command the serpent, and it shall bite them.
\q1
\v 4 \x + \xo 9:4 \xt [Deut. 28:65] \x*And if they go into captivity before their enemies,
\q2 there I will command the sword, and it shall kill them;
\q1 \x + \xo 9:4 \xt See Jer. 21:10\x*and I will fix my eyes upon them
\q2 for evil and not for good.”
\b
\q1
\v 5 The Lord \nd God\nd* of hosts,
\q1 he who touches the earth and \x + \xo 9:5 \xt Ps. 46:6 \x*it melts,
\q2 and all who dwell in it mourn,
\q1 \x + \xo 9:5 \xt ch. 8:8\x*and all of it rises like the Nile,
\q2 \x + \xo 9:5 \xt ch. 8:8\x*and sinks again, like the Nile of Egypt;
\q1
\v 6 \x + \xo 9:6 \xt [Ps. 104:3, 5] \x*who builds his upper chambers in the heavens
\q2 and founds his vault upon the earth;
